# Frontend package manager config — pnpm only.
#
# Block packages younger than 7 days (10080 minutes). Defends against
# the typosquat / compromised-release window where a newly published
# version of a popular package turns out to be malicious or yanked.
# If a fresh package is genuinely required, override per-install with
# --ignore-workspace-root-check + explicit justification in the commit.
minimum-release-age=10080



#Why would a project do this?

#It's a security measure.

#Sometimes:

#An npm account gets hacked.
#Someone publishes a malicious version of a popular package.
#A package accidentally ships a broken release and quickly removes it.

#The first few hours or days after a release are when these problems are most likely to be discovered.

#Waiting a week reduces the chance that your project pulls in a bad package.

#Someone publishes reactt instead of react (a typosquatting attack).